extends _skeleton-component

block append variables             
	- var currentPage = 'documentation'

block component
	.card.shadow-sm.mb-3
		.card-header.px-4.py-3
			h5#quick-start.mb-0.contains-anchor Quick start
				a(href='#quick-start').anchor  #
		.card-body.p-4
			p.mb-0 Looking to start your project quickly? Just unzip the 
				code #{theme}.zip
				| . We have precompiled and packaged everything in the 
				code pages
				|  directory for you. Start editing the
				a(href='page-starter.html').text-decoration-none  
					code /page-starter.html
				|  with a text or code editor, save it, and open the file in your favourite browser to see the changes.

	.card.shadow-sm.mb-3
		.card-header.px-4.py-3
			h5#setting-up-build-system.mb-0.contains-anchor Setting up Build system
				a(href='#setting-up-build-system').anchor  #
		.card-body.p-4
			p Unzip the 
				code #{theme}.zip
				|  to any folder and open a command line or terminal at that location.
				| theme's dev tools require 
				a(href='https://nodejs.org/en/' target='_blank') Node
				|  and 
				a(href='https://git-scm.com/' target='_blank') Git
				|  . If you do not have them in your machine, please install their latest stable version from their corresponding website. As you have 
				span.font-weight-black.text-black Node and Git installed and accessible from your terminal or command line
				| , install 
				a(href="https://gulpjs.com/" target='_blank') Gulp CLI
				|  package 
				|  globally with the following command:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					npm i gulp-cli -g

			p.mt-4 When you’re done, install the rest of the theme’s dependencies with:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					npm i

			p.mt-4 Now run:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					gulp

			p.mt-4 Running gulp will compile the SCSS, transpile the javascript, copy all required libraries form 
				code node_modules
				|  to the corresponding 
				code pages/assets/ 
				|  directory and will open a browser window to 
				code pages/index.html
			p All of the following folders are monitored for changes, which will tell the browser to reload automatically after any changes are made:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					pages/*.html
					pages/assets/fonts/
					pages/assets/video/
					pages/assets/img/
					scss/ 
					js/

			p.mt-4 Now you can edit any html file from 
				code pages
				| , change SCSS variable with 
				code _user-variables.scss
				| , or write your own SCSS code in 
				code scss/_user.scss

			.alert.alert-warning Running the 
				code gulp
				|  command will discard and regenerate all the files in following directories:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					js/bootstrap/
					scss/bootstrap/
					pages/assets/css/
					pages/assets/js/
					pages/assets/lib/

			p.mt-4 Hit 
				code Ctrl+C
				|  or just close the command line window to stop the server.

			p Happy editing!

	h3.mt-6.mb-4.contains-anchor#rtl RTL
		a(href='#rtl').anchor #
	.card.shadow-sm.mb-3
		.card-header.px-4.py-3
			h5#setting-up-html.mb-0.contains-anchor Setting up HTML
				a(href='#setting-up-html').anchor  #
		.card-body.p-4
			p Your theme comes with a built-in automated rlt feature. 
				a(href=`${CWD}index-rtl.html`) Here
				|  is the example. To use rtl, set the 
				code dir='rtl'
				|  in your html like:
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					#{'<html dir=\'rtl\'>...</html>'}
			p.mt-4 And use the rtl stylesheet instead of 
				code theme.css
				| :
			pre
				code.lang-html.
					#{'<link href="assets/css/theme-rtl.css" rel="stylesheet">'}
	.card.shadow-sm.mb-3
		.card-header.px-4.py-3
			h5#setting-up-buil-tools.mb-0.contains-anchor Setting up build tools
				a(href='#setting-up-buil-tools').anchor #
		.card-body.p-4
			p To compile 
				code theme-rtl.css
				|  directly with the built tools run:
			pre
				code.language-javascript.
					#{'product scss:rtl'}

			p.mt-4 To set your build tool in 
				code rtl
				|  mode, change the following code located at the last line of your 
				code gulpfile.js
			h5 From:
			pre
				code.language-javascript.
					#{'gulp.task(\'default\', product.series(\'copy:dependency\', \'scss\', \'js\', product.parallel(\'watch\', \'serve\')));'}
			h5 to:
			pre
				code.language-javascript.
					#{'gulp.task(\'default\', product.series(\'copy:dependency\', \'scss:rtl\', \'js\', product.parallel(\'watch\', \'serve\')));'}

			p.mt-4 And Also update the 
				code gulp watch
				|  to call the 
				code scss:rtl
				|  task by updating the following code at 
				code line 332
				|  in your 
				code gulpfile.js
				| : 
			h5 From:
			pre
				code.language-javascript.
					#{'gulp.watch(Paths.SCSS.ALL, product.series(\'scss\'));'}
			h5 to:
			pre
				code.language-javascript.
					#{'gulp.watch(Paths.SCSS.ALL, product.series(\'scss:rtl\'));'}



